When `do_using_dynamic` is false and section_headers is NULL, iterating through it and calling `display_relocations(section, ...)` with a NULL section pointer causes the crash at line 1318 when dereferencing `section->sh_type`.

Let me verify this is the actual trigger path. In `process_relocs` at lines 1468-1567, when `do_using_dynamic` is true, it processes dynamic relocations directly using indices into `dynamic_info`. But at line 1568-1608, when `do_using_dynamic` is false, it iterates through `section_headers`. This is where the vulnerability occurs - if `process_section_headers` fails and sets `section_headers` to NULL, the loop still executes and passes NULL to `display_relocations`.

